    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nA `Painter` has been given instructions to go to the food truck, but the `Painter` hasn't yet been created!\r\n\r\nFix the program by creating another `Painter`.\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/100f4803c0c2550d3b6b6d4820d1ad0d-choiceB.gif)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nTo create a `Painter`, use\r\n\r\n   ```\r\n   painter_name = Painter()\r\n   ```\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n\r\n   ```\r\n   alicia = Painter()\r\n   ```\r\n   \r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-hand-back-point-right\"></i> **By the way!** Reference the Python documentation to learn more about creating a new `Painter` object.",
